<section class="bg-ideal-blue-dark pt-10 lg:py-20">
  <div class="container mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center justify-center">
    <!--Text-->
    <div class="lg:w-1/2 flex flex-col items-center lg:items-end">
      <!--Container for text to align them-->
      <div class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <h2 class="font-semibold text-4xl text-white pb-4 text-center">Why an Instrument Rating?</h2>
        <div class="text-white px-6 lg:pl-0 lg:pr-8 p-text">
          <p class="pb-5">
            Passing your private pilot checkride and receiving your private Pilot Certificate is a remarkable accomplishment, and an Instrument Rating takes your flying skills to a whole new level. When you get your instrument rating, you'll acquire the skills to confidently navigate aircraft solely by instruments, regardless of external visual references. This mastery of precision flying opens doors to new flying experiences and enhances your overall piloting skills. Imagine confidently handling complex flight scenarios, from navigating through challenging weather conditions to performing pinpoint approaches.
            <br><br>
            <span class="font-bold underline font-sans text-3xl">The Instrument Rating makes you a better and safer pilot</span>
          </p>
          <p class="pb-5">
            Getting your instrument rating is the next step after your private pilot certificate and allows you to fly in challenging weather conditions.
          </p>
  
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!--Picture-->
    <div class="lg:w-1/2 lg:py-6 lg:flex flex-col items-center">
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center">
        <%=image_tag "in-between-clouds-ifr.webp", alt: "Flying in between the clouds on an instrument flight", class: "lg:w-5/6"%>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="bg-gradient-to-t from-blue-300 to-blue-50 pt-10 lg:py-20">
  <div class="container mx-auto flex flex-col lg:flex-row-reverse items-center justify-center">
    <!--Text-->
    <div class="lg:w-1/2 flex flex-col items-center lg:items-end">
      <h2 class="font-semibold text-4xl text-black pb-4 text-center lg:px-20">How to Get Your Instrument Rating</h2>
      <div class="text-black px-10 p-text lg:max-w-xl">
        <p class="pb-5">
          Ideal Aviation is dedicated to supporting you on your journey towards becoming an instrument pilot. Whether you're a private pilot seeking to enhance your skills or you have aviation as a career in mind, we're here for you. Our program seamlessly blends comprehensive ground school instruction with immersive hands on flight training, equipping you with the expertise to confidently navigate and operate aircraft relying solely on instruments.
        </p>
        <p class="pb-5">
          Learn how to better understand tough weather scenarios and execute instrument approaches to land the aircraft safely. Our experienced certified flight instructors (CFII) will help you become a better and safer pilot.
        </p>
        <p class="pb-5">
          <span class="font-bold font-sans text-2xl">Choose Ideal Aviation and Start Your Instrument Training Today</span>
        </p>
        <%= link_to "CONTACT US",  contact_path, data: { turbo: false }, class: "btn-primary"%>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lg:w-1/2">
      <%= image_tag "pilot-flying-on-ifr-flight.webp", alt: "Pilot smiling for a picture in the middle of an IFR flight at Ideal Aviation", class: ""%>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="bg-blue-900 py-20">
  <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center justify-center">
    <!--Text-->
    <div class="lg:w-1/2 flex flex-col items-center lg:items-end">
      <!--Container for text to align them-->
      <div class="lg:w-3/4 lg:text-left">
        <h2 class="font-extrabold text-4xl text-white pb-4">Eligibility Requirements for an Instrument Rating</h2>
        <div class="text-base text-white px-6 lg:pl-0 lg:pr-8">
          <p class="pb-5">
            Achieving an Instrument Rating opens up a new realm of aviation expertise. This coveted rating demands a solid foundation as you venture into the intricacies of instrument piloting.
          </p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-extrabold text-2xl">
            To qualify, you must demonstrate proficiency in:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside border-b-2 pb-3 pl-3">
              <li class="mb-2">Reading, speaking, writing, and comprehending English</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Holding a current private pilot certificate or applying for one alongside the instrument rating</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Receiving ground training from an authorized instructor or completing a home study course for aeronautical knowledge</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Passing the instrument rating knowledge test with instructor endorsement</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Completing the required flight training</li>
              <p class="text-xs mt-4">Reference <a class="text-blue-300" href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-14/chapter-I/subchapter-D/part-61#61.65">14 CFR ยง61.65</a> for the entire list of eligibility requirements.</p>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-extrabold text-2xl">
            As you embark on this journey, you'll delve into a comprehensive curriculum, including topics like:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside border-b-2 pb-3 pl-3">
              <li class="mb-2">IFR flight planning and filing</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Navigation during departure, en route, and arrival in IFR conditions</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Understanding airplane systems for IFR operations</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Instrument flight deck checks</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Air traffic control clearances and procedures</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Various instrument approach procedures</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Emergency operations within IFR</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Weather information analysis</li>
            </ul>
          </p>
          <p class="my-2 pb-5 font-extrabold text-2xl">
            Your journey towards the Instrument Rating also involves achieving specific aeronautical flight experience:
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside border-b-2 pb-3 pl-3">
              <li class="mb-2">Clock in a minimum of 50 hours of cross-country pilot-in-command (PIC) time</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Log 40 hours of instrument time, whether actual or simulated</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Receive at least 15 hours of flight time from an authorized instructor</li>
              <li class="mb-2">Conquer a cross-country flight of 250 nautical miles, meeting specific instrument requirements</li>
              <p class="text-xs mt-4">Reference <a class="text-blue-300" href="https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-14/chapter-I/subchapter-D/part-61#61.65">14 CFR ยง61.65</a> for the entire list of eligibility requirements.</p>
            </ul>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row pt-10 pb-0 lg:py-10 bg-gray-800">
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300 border-b-2 lg:border-b-0">
    <div class="p-10 "><%=image_tag "ideal_group.webp", alt: "Group picture of Ideal Aviation team", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 1. Emark On Flight Training</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      In this pivotal phase, you'll embark on a 50-hour cross-country flight journey, immersing yourself in diverse terrains, varied airspace, and intricate navigation scenarios. Guided by our seasoned instructors, you'll amass invaluable expertise in planning and executing cross-country flights, refining your mastery in flight planning, navigation precision, and effective communication. Furthermore, 40 dedicated hours will be invested in harnessing your instrument skills, teaching you the art of flying solely by instrument references. You'll become adept at precision approaches, mastering holding patterns, and navigating through instrument meteorological conditions (IMC).
    </p>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4 py-5">
      Our team of expert instructors is committed to providing personalized guidance and immersive training, ensuring you not only become a proficient instrument pilot but also develop the unwavering confidence to conquer real-world aviation challenges.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300 border-b-2 lg:border-b-0  lg:h-full">
    <div class="p-10 lg:order-last"><%=image_tag "ideal_group.webp", alt: "Group picture of Ideal Aviation team", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 2. Mastery through Written Assessment</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      Attaining true mastery of instrument flying necessitates a firm grasp of the underlying theoretical principles. During this phase, your focus will be on acing the instrument written exam. Our all-encompassing educational resources and experienced mentors are at your disposal, aiding you in fully comprehending the subject matter essential for success in the exam.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4 py-5">
      Ranging from the intricacies of Instrument Flight Rules (IFR) regulations and protocols to delving into meteorological theories and instrument-based navigation, we're committed to furnishing you with the proficiency and analytical skills necessary for excelling in the written assessment. Our approach includes mock tests, comprehensive deliberations, and personalized guidance, all intended to ensure your readiness to confidently conquer the exam. This phase will establish a sturdy bedrock for your journey into instrument flight training.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300 border-b-2 lg:border-b-0">
    <div class="p-10 "><%=image_tag "ideal_group.webp", alt: "Group picture of Ideal Aviation team", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 3. Embarking on an Extensive Cross-Country Voyage</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      Embark on a thrilling and pivotal stage of your instrument training by immersing yourself in a substantial long cross-country flight. This phase represents a remarkable milestone, offering you the chance to apply your newly acquired instrument prowess in authentic scenarios. As you undertake this journey, you'll master advanced navigation techniques and employ intricate instrument procedures. Our adept instructors will be your guiding light as you meticulously plan and flawlessly execute a demanding cross-country expedition, braving diverse weather patterns, intricate airspace, and varied topography.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4 py-5">
      This firsthand encounter will sharpen your decision-making acumen, elevate your situational consciousness, and foster a profound comprehension of instrument flight dynamics. Confronting the intricacies of long-distance aviation will nurture the self-assurance and adeptness needed to adeptly navigate the instrument realm, ensuring your secure arrival at your intended destination.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="flex flex-col items-center lg:w-1/2 p-text text-gray-300">
    <div class="p-10 lg:order-last"><%=image_tag "ideal_group.webp", alt: "Group picture of Ideal Aviation team", class: "rounded-lg"%></div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold pb-4 font-sans mx-5 text-center uppercase font-header text-white">Step 4. Culminating Evaluation - The Checkride</h3>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4">
      The pinnacle of your journey towards obtaining your instrument rating arrives in the form of meticulous preparation for the impending checkride. Our committed instructors are dedicated to furnishing you with an exhaustive checkride training regimen, ensuring your complete readiness to demonstrate your adeptness in instrument flying. Through intensive rehearsals, lifelike simulated checkride scenarios, and comprehensive feedback loops, we will meticulously refine your proficiencies and knowledge to surpass the evaluation benchmarks.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base w-3/4 py-5">
      Our focus will be on perfecting your precision in instrument approaches, flawlessly executing intricate instrument procedures, and unveiling your impeccable decision-making prowess. With our unwavering support and guidance, you will approach the checkride with self-assurance and thorough preparation, poised to exhibit your expertise and secure the instrument rating that you've diligently earned.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
